---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Wayfinders — Christian career discernment">
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1>A different kind of career conversation</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Wayfinders is a small, free, mentor-led cohort for UK Christians making real mid-career decisions &mdash; not about ordained ministry, but about the rest of your working life.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>
        You're a Christian in your 20s&ndash;50s. You work in a secular role. You're facing a real decision &mdash; sector switch, promotion, redundancy, "should I leave the City," "is this still where I'm meant to be" &mdash; and you want to think it through with people who take both your faith and your career seriously.
      </p>
      <p>
        You've looked around and found plenty of content about faith and work, but not many places where someone will sit with you while you actually decide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Who this isn't for</h2>
      <p>
        If you're exploring ordained ministry, there are better-resourced places for that conversation. If you're in crisis, we'd rather you got the right help first and joined a future cohort when you're ready. If you're looking for a job board or a networking event, this isn't that either.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Each cohort runs for <strong>eight weeks</strong>. You get a mentor &mdash; someone who's made cross-sector career moves themselves &mdash; and five structured sessions:
      </p>
      <ol class="session-list">
        <li>The decision in front of you &mdash; what is it actually?</li>
        <li>Story so far &mdash; what has God already done with your work?</li>
        <li>Counsel layer &mdash; Scripture, wise voices, lived examples</li>
        <li>Test the move &mdash; small bets, what would you regret?</li>
        <li>Decision + sending &mdash; name the next step</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Two sessions are with the full cohort (6&ndash;8 people). Three are with your mentor. All online, at times that work for the group.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What it costs</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing. Wayfinders is free. Mentors are not paid. There is no premium tier, no follow-on coaching offer, no membership scheme. <a href="/principles">Read why.</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What happens after</h2>
      <p>
        Cohort graduates join a small alumni network &mdash; a standing group of people who've been through the same process and stay connected for ongoing peer support, prayer, and the kind of conversation you can't have at a networking event.
      </p>
    </section>

    <aside class="highlight-box" aria-label="Cohort status">
      <p class="highlight-heading"><strong>Next cohort</strong></p>
      <p class="highlight-body">Applications will open soon. <a href="/apply">Read more about applying.</a></p>
    </aside>

    <section>
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>
        Wayfinders is run by <strong>Ben Hollebon</strong>, a digital strategist based in the UK who works at the intersection of technology, institutions, and people. Ben has spent his career navigating cross-sector moves and helping organisations think clearly about change &mdash; and has had enough conversations with Christians wrestling with career decisions to know the gap is real.
      </p>
      <p>
        This isn't a business. It's a small thing done properly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="cta-block">
      <a href="/apply" class="btn">Apply for the next cohort</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .session-list {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .session-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-block {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
